<item>
            <title>[SPARK-21225] decrease the Mem using for variable &apos;tasks&apos; in function resourceOffers</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-21225</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;    In the function &apos;resourceOffers&apos;, It declare a variable &apos;tasks&apos; for storage the tasks which have  allocated a executor. It declared like this:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;b&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#d04437&quot;&gt;val tasks = shuffledOffers.map(o =&amp;gt; new ArrayBuffer&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;TaskDescription&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;(o.cores))&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But, I think this code only conside a situation for that one task per core. If the user config the &quot;spark.task.cpus&quot; as 2 or 3, It really don&apos;t need so much space. I think It can motify as follow:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#14892c&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;val tasks = shuffledOffers.map(o =&amp;gt; new ArrayBuffer&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;TaskDescription&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;(Math.ceil(o.cores*1.0/CPUS_PER_TASK).toInt))&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
